Serve with mustard/shoyu sauce, if desired.

title: good for you, chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in
mixture
of
egg and milk, then shake in bag with herb
mix.
Place
oil in large flat pan and place chicken, skin side down.
Bake
in
a
oven for 30 minutes, then turn chicken over for 15 minutes more.

title: strawberry cake dessert
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle marshmallows on the bottom.
Combine strawberries and gelatin and set aside (use the syrup and don't add water to the gelatin).

title: spiced apple spread(using sure-jell light)
directions: Combine
pectin
with 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Mix applesauce and spices in large bowl.
Add pectin mixture gradually to
fruit, stirring
vigorously.
Set
aside
for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir
remaining
sugar gradually into fruit mixture until sugar is dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Pour into plastic containers; cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24
hours. Spread is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerator up
to
3 weeks or freeze extra containers up to 1 year.
Thaw in refrigerator. Makes about 5 (1 cup) containers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together
and
bake
at
for 1 hour.
You can saute the onion and celery in the butter if you like, first.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: sweet potato sausage ball
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Roll into balls and place on greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fantastic squash casserole
directions: *Dried minced green onion can be used as a substitute.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in saucepan until well mixed.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Cook until thick.
Serve over ice cream.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add dry ingredients alternately with tomato soup.

title: polish raisin-walnut puffs
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, bring raisins, water and butter to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in walnuts, lemon peel, juice and vanilla.
Cool completely.
Thaw puff pastry for 20 minutes and unfold.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each sheet to a 9 x 15-inch rectangle, then cut into 3-inch squares.
Put about 2 teaspoons of filling in the center of each square; moisten corners of pastry with water and bring together to make a four cornered puff.
Press firmly to seal.
Bake on a cookie sheet in a preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until golden.
Unbaked puffs may be wrapped tightly in plastic wrap and frozen until ready to bake.
Makes 30 puffs.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients except peaches in baking dish.
Lay peaches on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: white bread
directions: Mix 2 cups water, 2 packages yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar. Let mix double. Add 2 cups very warm water, salt and oil; add flour until stiff and knead.
Put in greased pan and raise.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: stew
directions: Cook ingredients until tender.
Tiny shell macaroni, 1/2 package.
Add not too long before other ingredients are done.

title: calizonas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place frozen bread in bread pans and let thaw.
Do not let rise, just thaw.
Scramble sausage in a skillet until browned.
Shred cheese(s).
Pinch bread into 3 to 4 separate sections (each loaf).
Butter hands and press flat and stretch dough until about 6 inches across.
Add sausage 4 to 5 tablespoons each on pressed dough.
Add cheese about 1/3 cup each.
Fold over to make a pastry like fold.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: family-styled short ribs
directions: Brown short ribs on all sides in oil.
Pour off drippings. Season with salt and pepper.
Add water, bouillon, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and the onion slices.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Pour out cooking liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Use water if needed.
Thicken the liquid for gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: frozen chocolate delight(good summer dessert)
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; set aside to cool.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on spinach salad.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put oatmeal into blender in small amounts and blend until it turns to powder.
Measure first and then blend.
Mix all dry ingredients together and then mix with sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Make golf ball sized cookies and place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: old-fashioned sweet potato pie *
directions: Boil sweet potatoes, peel and mash, then add margarine, syrup, white sugar, flour and seasoning.
Bake in 9-inch crust.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vanilla-butter and nut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine, sugar and salt for 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Fold in flavoring. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Start in COLD oven and do not open door while baking.
Cool on rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese-spinach soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in spinach and cheese. Cook and stir until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple sheet cake(easy and good for potlucks!)
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet pan.
Mix all together and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Transfer to baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mother's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with tortilla strips, hamburger meat, tomatoes, beans, onion and cheese.
Mix soups together with small amount of water and spread over top of casserole.
Begin layering again and end up with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: mom's barbecue buns
directions: In a
large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, dry milk solids, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add margarine.

title: chocolate syrup for drinks
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Add chocolate, salt and the cornstarch dissolved in cold water.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Store in a jar in refrigerator.

title: key lime pie
directions: Thoroughly mix the gelatin, sugar and salt in a saucepan. Beat together the egg yolks, lime juice and water; stir into the gelatin mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until the mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from the heat; stir in the grated peel.
Add the food coloring sparingly to give a pale green color.

Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Beat the egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold the gelatin mixture into the egg whites; fold the whipped cream.
Pile into the pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Spread with additional whipped cream and edge with grated lime.

title: country cookies
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, cream shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until blended.
Add flour.
Sprinkle baking soda and salt over top.
Beat until no traces of flour can be seen.
With a wooden spoon, work in oats and coconut.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a big bowl.
Add shortening, peanut butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: mother ruth's pimiento cheese
directions: Blend in mixer, blender or food processor. Add salt, pepper, hot sauce and garlic powder to taste. Fix a day ahead and keep in sealed container. Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator. Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: easy baked crock pot beans
directions: Brown meat, green peppers and onions. Combine all ingredients in slow cooker for 4 to 6 hours on low.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut flowerettes from broccoli.
Layer broccoli, raisins, onion, bacon and water chestnuts in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: stain glass candy
directions: Heat first three ingredients to 290° with a candy thermometer. Remove from heat. Quickly add flavoring oil and food coloring. Pour onto cookie sheet that has been covered with aluminum foil. Let harden. Peel foil off. Hold one end up with one hand and break candy into small pieces with back of a spoon. Be sure to store in an air tight container.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; cool.
Combine all ingredients. Marinate at least 12 hours.
Drain.

title: broccoli-beef pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic.
Add milk and softened cream cheese.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add moderate amount of hot mixture to beaten egg. Return to mixture in skillet.
Cook until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Set aside.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with bananas, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: jiffy oatmeal bread
directions: Lightly grease 2 loaf pans.
Put salt, molasses, oil and oats in a large bowl.
Add boiling water.
When the mixture is lukewarm, add eggs and yeast; let stand until yeast is dissolved, then add flour.
Stir and let stand 20 minutes (no kneading).
Turn out on floured board; knead and cut into 4 equal parts.
Put 2 parts in each bread pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: skillet hamburger pie
directions: In skillet, cook beef, celery and onion until meat is browned and vegetables are crisp and tender.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt, beans, gravy mix and 1 cup water.
Simmer to thicken and blend flavors.
Whip potatoes according to directions.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Top with paprika and shredded cheese. Cover.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni-cheese salad
directions: Add all ingredients to the macaroni.
Serves 6.

title: microwave chili con queso dip
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High power for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave for 1 additional minute.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate filled eggs(easter treat)
directions: One egg at a time, use a pin or the tip of a sharp knife to make a small hole in the top of each egg and a larger hole in the bottom (3/8-inch).
(Hold egg over bowl.)
Blow the egg white and yolk into the bowl (can be used for cooking).
Carefully fill the egg with water and blow it out again.
Rinse repeatedly to remove all traces of egg.
Let the eggs drain and dry (an old egg carton is good for this) in a warm place for several days.
Melt the chocolate over very low heat, stirring constantly, to 125°.
When completely melted, remove from heat and stir constantly while cooling until a dab placed just above your lip feels cool.
Pour chocolate into hollow eggs.
Let cool.
Makes a great Easter surprise.

title: pasta with cauliflower
directions: First, brown bread crumbs in a nonstick frying pan over medium heat.
Stir constantly; pour into a bowl.
Set aside for later use.
Clean cauliflower.
Cut into small flowerets.
Cover bottom of 4-quart pot with olive oil.
Add garlic and cauliflower. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Add chicken broth.
Turn heat to high; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix crackers and oil until well coated.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in Ziploc bag and enjoy.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sherbet.
Allow to cool and thicken.
When mixture is thick, add pineapple, oranges and bananas. Fold in whipped cream.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk; bring to a boil.
Cool to room temperature. Beat in powdered sugar until like fudge.
Stir in nuts; pour in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap and refrigerate to set. Better overnight.

title: fruit punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine sugar and water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice, grape juice, tea and grapefruit juices.
Mix well (chill thoroughly).
At serving time, stir in ginger ale and garnish with orange slices studded with whole cloves, lemon slices and cherries.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells. Bake 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: bean-pea salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables well.
Add to chopped vegetables.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, bring vinegar, oil, and sugar to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cut the Velveeta into 5 blocks.
Place in crock-pot on high. Add jar of salsa.
Stir frequently until all cheese is melted. Reduce heat to low and continue to stir occasionally.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: sudden russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 teaspoonfuls of mixture to one cup boiling water for each cup of this tea.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp. Add onion and seasonings to bacon grease. Simmer for a few minutes. Add potatoes and crumble bacon on top. Serve hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Then mix in lard like pie dough.
Add eggs, vanilla or lemon flavoring and buttermilk with soda. Roll out and cut.

title: spinach souffle pie
directions: Do not prick the pastry shell before baking.
Partially bake the pastry shell in a 450° oven for 5 minutes; remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine and sugar, blend in eggs.
Add flour; mix well.
Spread on bottom and 2 inches high around sides of 9-inch cheesecake spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown meat and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add onion and green pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes and then drain off any excess grease.
Next, add tomato and mushroom soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add macaroni and beans with meat mixture in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and place in oven at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 8.

title: good corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Thicken with 1/4 cup cornstarch, dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil again.
Seal in jars, 6 or 7 pints.
I make this at Christmas time and use it for gifts.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water in a covered saucepan or microwave until crisp-tender; drain. Place broccoli in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch (2-quart) baking dish; set aside. Combine chicken, soup, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and curry powder; spoon over broccoli. Top with bread cubes and butter. Bake chicken casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Chicken casserole serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil on low heat until soft ball forms in cold water.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pan and let cool.
Cut into very small pieces.
Candy is very rich.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut. Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: drum stick cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13 glass pan. Spread ice cream over Cocoa Krispie mixture.
Spread hot fudge over ice cream.
Sprinkle peanuts on last.
Freeze overnight. Serve frozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries and pineapple in cake pan.
Stir in coconut. Pour cake mix on top of mixture.
Slice butter in pats and place on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sarah's strawberry jello
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Chill 1/2 of this mixture.
Spread sour cream over chilled Jell-O.
Top with rest of the Jell-O mixture.
Chill and cut to serve.
Serves 15.

title: cauliflower with cheese
directions: Microwave whole cauliflower in a covered casserole dish for 10 minutes. Mix together the mayonnaise, grated cheese and mustard in a small bowl.
Pour on cauliflower and microwave on High for 3 minutes, uncovered.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well and put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot ham and cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower and/or broccoli in a small amount of boiling salted water.
Cover until crisp-tender. Drain well. Remove from pan.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in the same pan.
Stir in flour. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is very thick and begins to bubble.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in ham, mushrooms and cooked vegetables.
Turn in a 2-quart casserole pan. Combine bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted margarine or butter.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll very thin on floured surface and cut out with favorite cookie cutters. Decorate, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot fat, about 3/4-inch deep.
Turn each puff when brown on one side, 3 to 5 minutes required.
(These may also be fried in deep fat.)

title: dearing street casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, saute celery, onions, green pepper and mushrooms in butter. Combine with rice, shrimp, crab and mushroom soup. Add salt and pepper. Pour into a buttered baking dish, sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs. Place baking dish in a larger pan of water and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine and vanilla.
Add sugar and milk (1 spoon at a time) until desired consistency.

title: irish creme
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Chill overnight and enjoy.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix next 3 ingredients for chili.
In separate pan melt cheese, then add cream.
Then add to chili. Serve over Doritos.
Top the taco (chili sauce) with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Top salad with Thousand Island dressing.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Puree basil, nuts and garlic.
Mix in cheese.
Add oil while machine is running.
Toss into any textured pasta.
Sprinkle top with cheese if desired or extra nuts.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and flour.
Blend thoroughly. Knead dough in 2 balls.
Roll balls paper thin into 16-inch circles.
Roll up like jelly rolls.
Cut with sharp knife or piece of thread in 1/4-inch strips.
Unwind strips and store in airtight container until ready to use.
Drop into boiling soup; allow to cook for 2 minutes before serving soup.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with King's Hawaiian bread.

title: pecan pie (1)
directions: Beat eggs lightly, mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325°F for about 45 min.
Put foil over top if crust gets too dark.

title: john wayne beans
directions: Cook bacon until almost done.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add ground beef; cook until done.
Add green chilies, tomatoes, soup and beans.
Just before serving stir in grated Cheddar cheese.
Add German Polish sausage when you add the beans.

title: butternut squash
directions: Wash squash and cut in half, lengthwise.
Remove seeds and string fiber.
Sprinkle with salt.
Dot with butter.
Add one tablespoon of honey or syrup to each half squash.
Place in a baking pan in oven at 375°.
Bake until tender about 45 minutes. Baste occasionally with the butter-honey mixture.
After squash has browned, which will take 30 minutes, add a little water to the pan. Cover for remainder of baking period.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it spins a thread.
Beat egg whites.
Pour half of syrup mixture over whites and beat at medium speed.
Cook other half of syrup until hard-ball stage (250° to 266° on candy thermometer).
Add to the egg white mixture and beat by hand until stiff.
Add vanilla (and nuts if desired). Put by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: ham-and-cheese pie
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, separate into 8 triangles. Fit triangles into a 9-inch pie plate, pressing edges together to seal. Combine chopped ham and next 4 ingredients, spoon into pie plate. Cut remaining 3 triangles into thin strips; arrange over mixture. Bake on lower oven rack at 325 degrees for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni, cheese sauce, luncheon meat and green pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until done.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Heat to boiling 7-Up and drained pineapple juice; dissolve jello with this.
Pour into square or rectangle container.
Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and almost all nuts (leave a few to sprinkle on top).
Mix with jello and chill.

title: filling a trifle bowl
directions: Break up or slice cake to fit bottom of trifle rifle bowl (or glass bowl).
Brush liberally with chocolate liqueur.
Cover with 1 layer of fruit and drizzle with sludge.
Spread on whipped cream. Repeat layers until top of bowl is reached.
Drizzle chocolate sauce on top.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onion fine.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Cover again with hot water and let come to boil.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain dry and add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Cook for 15 minutes and pack in hot jars. Process in water bath can at 212° for 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: curried rabbit
directions: Soak the rabbit in salted water about 30 minutes.
Wash and drain.
Saute onion, garlic and ginger in butter.
Add curry powder, chili, salt and sage.
Heat for about 1 minute and add the tomatoes.
Saute and add the yogurt.
Allow to cook with stirring for 20 to 30 minutes or so.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat and combine with other ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Good with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Cook for 10 minutes at 375°.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: chocolate tea cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla. Sift flour with cocoa and salt. Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture. Add pecans and mix well. Shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. While, warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pour into greased loaf pan.
Cover top with ketchup and bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook all until thick (except shell).
Cool and pour over 1 1/2 cups sliced peaches that have been placed in pie shell.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar in saucepan.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat eggs, one at a time; add to butter mixture.
Add flour and pecans.
Pour mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed rigatoni
directions: Saute in pan.
When cooked, stuff into partially cooked large rigatoni.
In baking dish, put layer of rigatoni and cover with spaghetti sauce over all.
Put in oven at 350° for 30 minutes to consume.

title: microwave oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together; coat chicken.
Arrange pieces, skin side up, in rectangular dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch) with thickest part toward edges.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave until done, 8 to 12 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mama susanna's chicken
directions: Pour half the cooking wine in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken, artichokes, olives, onion, garlic and oregano in and then add the rest of the wine.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Garnish with Romano cheese.
Put over your favorite pasta.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot 4 hours or 2 hours at 325° in oven.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Cook and drain spinach.
Add all ingredients to egg mixture and stir. Melt margarine in 10-inch square pan.
Pour mixture in; bake 30 minutes.
Let set after baking for about 10 minutes.

title: glazed bacon strips
directions: Roll each slice of bacon in brown sugar, covering both sides. Place on broiler pan or rack.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 30 minutes. Keep checking until bacon is browned and fat cooked from it.
Place cooked bacon on foil to cool.
It will crisp as it cools.
Serve at room temperature.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Mix all together and cook until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Add nuts and beat until creamy.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften and mix together.
Make into 2 or more rolls.
Roll in chili powder or Parmesan cheese.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and Tang gently with fruit mixture.
Chill. May be used as salad or dessert.

title: cinnamon sugar treats
directions: Thaw pie crust for 10 to 20 minutes in pan.
Prick sides of crust thoroughly with a fork.
Dot bottom and sides of thawed pie crust with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 8 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cool, then cut into pieces for serving.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts and corn is tender.
This recipe can be doubled easily and kept warm in a crock pot.

title: all meat spaghetti with sauce
directions: Prepare spaghetti by directions on package.
Mix ground beef, onions and salt; cook until well done.
Drain; set aside.

title: brown rice #3
directions: Brown onions in margarine.
Add to remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat until bubbly; pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until biscuits are golden brown. Refrigerate any leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Add heated liquids to flour mixture and beat.
Add 2 beaten eggs and enough flour to make soft dough.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well, maybe overnight.
Mix with mixer, all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Roll into crushed nuts.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: nutty glazed pastries(easy and tasty!)
directions: Blend powdered sugar, butter or margarine and water.
Add vanilla extract. (Or if in a hurry, you can use white vanilla or almond flavor canned frosting.)

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water, salt and pepper.
Keep water over the top of beans.
Stir and discard bean pieces which float to the top.
Cover with fresh water.
Boil 1 hour; drain.
Return beans to kettle.
Add all ingredients and water to cover beans. Simmer several hours.
Stir occasionally (too much stirring causes beans to get mushy).
Always keep enough water in kettle.
Eat as is or add to chili, refried, etc.

title: czeck cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Blend well.
Gradually add flour and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pat half of batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread with filling.
Cover with remaining batter. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and salt.
Add to milk and butter. Cook until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook about 15 minutes longer until real thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: almond butter krunch
directions: Combine butter, sugar and 1/2 cup almonds in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Heat slowly to boiling point.
Boil gently until 305°, stirring constantly.
Pour into large buttered sheet pan sprinkled with 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Spread with spatula.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup almonds.
Cool and turn over and put rest of chocolate chips and almonds.
Place under broiler until chips melt.
Spread chocolate chips and rest of almonds.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream together graham crackers, margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Line bottom of 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 to 1 cup powdered sugar, and vanilla together and add to Cool Whip,
Mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers crust.
Spread cherry pie filling over whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator and chill for several hours before serving.

title: white potato pie
directions: Peel and quarter the white potatoes; boil them until tender. Put cooked potatoes in a large bowl.
Mash potatoes until smooth, then mix them with butter, sugar, salt, lemon and vanilla.
Add eggs, milk and baking powder; beat until smooth.
Add more sugar, if desired.
Pour mixture into pie crust shells and sprinkle lightly with grated coconut.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until done.

title: baked flounder
directions: Arrange fish in 9 x 13 inch baking dish,
lightly greased or sprayed with Pam.
Drizzle dressing over fish, then sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° or until fish are flaky.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Divide the quantities by 450 and you will have plenty of mincemeat for two 10-inch pies.

title: chicken salad with vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs and peas, then carefully fold in eggs and peas.
Place on crisp lettuce leaf and arrange quarters of tomatoes around.

title: dessert bars
directions: Mix melted oleo and brown sugar.
Let cool.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together; cut in the Crisco.
Beat the eggs in a one cup measuring cup; add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add to dry ingredients with vanilla.
Roll on floured covered surface; cut as desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut and form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Can use food coloring on coconut for holidays.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
May use mild or sharp cheese. May also use mild or hot sausage.

title: delightful cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle 3 tablespoons graham cracker crumbs in 9-inch pan. Set aside.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Bring 3/4 cup juice to boil and stir in gelatin.
Beat cottage cheese smooth.
Add egg yolks, skim milk, lemon juice, sweetener, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Blend in gelatin at low speed.
Chill.
Stir occasionally until thick, but not set, about 1 hour.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, then fold into gelatin mixture by hand.
Spoon over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Add pineapple tidbits on top.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
In separate bowl, mix beans, corn, tomatoes, onions, peppers, cheese, and bacon.
Mix in layers of vegetable mixture.
Mix sour cream and picante sauce together. Combine with cornbread and vegetable mixture just before serving.

title: broccoli or cauliflower soup
directions: Cook vegetables in large covered saucepan in chicken broth until almost tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Do not drain.
Set aside.
In another bowl, gradually add cream of potato soup; mix thoroughly.
Blend water in cornstarch (in small cup).
Pour into potato soup mixture.
Mix together, then pour all white mixture into vegetables and broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly (on medium heat).

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Melt margarine in a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray.
Add cabbage and next 4 ingredients; cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with caraway seed; cover and cook 1 minute.
Yield:
5 cups.
Contains 39 calories per 1 cup serving.

title: date walnut balls
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Stir in sugar, egg yolk and dates.
Cook and stir over low heat 5 minutes or until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, peel and nuts. Cool.
Drop or roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Delicious!!
I double this recipe.

title: viking stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat and dredge in flour; set aside.
Fry bacon in large, heavy pot and brown beef in remaining bacon drippings.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add diced bacon, onion, garlic, tomato sauce, wine, broth and seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and continue to cook, uncovered, until vegetables are tender.
If desired, stew can be thickened. Mix 2 to 4 tablespoons flour with 2 cups water.
Stir into stew and heat to boiling.
Serves 8.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add egg, flour and all other ingredients; blend.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma wheeler's banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour mixture (including salt and soda), sifting, alternately with milk. Beat after each addition. Add vanilla and beat. Stir in mashed bananas and nuts. Pour into greased and floured rectangle pan. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put equal amount in two 9-inch square pans that have been sprayed with Pam or Cooking Ease.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for 35 minutes.
Chill in icebox and cut in bite-size pieces.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres.
Yields 180 bite-size squares.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over cherry filling.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: one bowl pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: barbecue party franks
directions: Mix all ingredients. Marinate overnight. Cook over medium heat in a saucepan for 30 minutes. Serve in a bowl with small amount of sauce; keep warm. Serve with toothpicks.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add green pepper, taco seasoning and tomatoes.
While meat mixture is cooking, cook noodles.
Rinse and drain noodles.
Put noodles in buttered baking dish.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Mix together.
Pour meat mixture over noodles and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Let set until solid in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn out of pan.

title: cherry dream salad
directions: Mix pineapple, pie
filling, condensed milk and nuts in a large bowl.
Fold in
whipped topping.
Place in mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
May be served immediately or chilled or frozen for later use.	Yield:	12 to 15 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Brown onion in oil on medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Add eggs.
When eggs are cooked, add rice and reduce heat.
Add 2 to 3 more tablespoons soy sauce and serve.

title: smoked salmon and dill rollups
directions: Combine the softened cream cheese with the fresh dill. Spread on the thin slices of smoked salmon and roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Chill.
Just before serving, cut the rollups into slices about 1/2 inch thick.

title: huevos mexicana(great for using up leftover hard-boiled eggs)
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stand 8 tortilla halves upright along sides of pan.
Cover center of pan with 4 tortilla halves.
Spread with 11 ounces of enchilada sauce.
Top with eggs. Mix next 7 ingredients.
Spread over eggs.
Top with remaining 12 tortilla halves, remaining enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with sour cream and olives.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat or in double boiler. Take off burner and add sugar, eggs, flour and salt mixed together and vanilla, stirring after each addition.
Add nuts last.
Bake in a 7 x 9-inch greased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Finely chop the pepper, onion and celery.
Flake the crabmeat. Combine all together, except for the cracker crumbs.
Place in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add Marshmallow Creme to blend. Add orange
juice
and	orange peel until well blended.
Good with chunks
of cantaloupe, honeydew melon, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Stir well.
Let stand
in
freezer
at
least
hours (overnight is preferable).
Make into small balls and place on wax paper.
Put back in
freezer
and freeze for about 1 hour. Melt 12 ounce chocolate chips with 3/4 of one bar of paraffin. Dip balls by toothpick into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.
Keep in freezer until set good.

title: spinach salad
directions: Shake well in jar.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut ends off the zucchini.
Cut zucchini lengthwise.
Do not pare the zucchini.
Scoop out pulp.
Cook (boil) pulp, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and eggs for 5 minutes.
Spoon into zucchini shells.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dressed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks, mash and mix with the remaining ingredients.
Fill white with the mixture and serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; pour into casserole dish. Top with roll of crushed Ritz crackers. Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Butter two large casseroles.
Heat oven to 325°.
Crush crackers into crumbs.
In skillet saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons butter.
In bowl mix soup, mushrooms and light cream. Put 1 fish fillet on bottom of each casserole.
Add a layer of mushroom sauce, then a layer of crumbs.
Continue layering seafoods in casseroles with a layer of sauce and crumbs between each.
Finish each with crumbs.
Cut remaining butter into thin pats and place on top.
Bake casseroles in a water bath for a little more than an hour.
This dish may be frozen.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9 x 13 baking dish. Layer the pan with frozen Tater Tots.
Mix together cream of chicken, sour cream and cheese in a separate bowl.	Pour over the Tater Tots and evenly distribute the mixture.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Place peaches in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm and if desired, with light cream, ice cream or hard sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool on wire rack. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream, if desired.
